@node "features" "Vokabi 2 guide - What's Vokabi 2?"
@next "requires"
@prev "Main"
@{b}What's Vokabi 2?@{ub}


Vokabi 2 is the first shareware vocabulary trainer for Amigas, with which you
can learn your words that way that you still know them half a year later and
you don't despair of feeding "vivid" instead of "lively".



@{b}For this purpose there are the following features:@{ub}


- @{"8 meanings" link "win_word" 0} a word and a language are supported, so you can learn grammar
  with it, too.

- The gender of nouns is tested automatically

- You can set the @{"direction of testing" link "win_fileset" 26} in percent

- Testing alternatively by "one of ten" or "feed all meanings". You can
  chose if the order of meanings is important or not.

- If you are tested by "one of ten" the nine wrong words are of the same
  part of speech as the tested word, if possible.

- If you want you are tested the other forms of the foreign language if
  the foreign language is given, too.

- Mistakes are automatically repeated according to a special system, so you
  can learn your words better.

- No word is tested twice before all words of the actual asking range
  are tested. This works also if you have learned another range inbetween.
  This information is saved!

- @{"References" link "win_word" 12}: Instead of having several entries
  words that are to be learned twice only get one mistake entry.

- @{"Unit marks" link "win_unitmarks" 0} divide many words into small ranges

- Fast navigation in huge vocabulary datas, too, because of joker search,
  "@{"Go to unit mark" link "menu_find" 10}" and "Remember position / Go to
  remembered position"

- flexible printing, you can print in files and / or dictionaries

- @{"MUI" link "mui" 0} user interface, so

- commodities interface

- online help, BubbleHelp and AmigaGuide

- ARexx port

- Localization (at the moment only English and German)
@endnode

@node "requires" "Vokabi 2 guide - Vokabi requires"
@next "desc_listWin"
@prev "features"
If you want to work with Vokabi 2 you should have:


- any AMIGA ;-)

- @{"MUI" link "mui" 0}, at least Version 3.3

- at least OS 2.0, if you want to use localization and online help you
  need OS 2.1

- Vokabi 2 should theoretically run with 512 KB of RAM. But you can't get
  an absolute number - it depends on how many words there are and how many
  meanings they have. But you should be able to work with small files (one
  or two school years or 1000-3000 words) with 1MB. So I say: The more RAM
  you have the better you can work with Vokabi 2.

  (Remark: Vokabi 2 gets its RAM in blocks which are as small as possible.
  So it works with strongly fragmented memory, too. But because of this often
  the operating system crashes because it hasn't enough RAM before Vokabi 2
  realizes it. Vokabi 2 tries to prevent this and quits safely if there are
  100 KB of RAM or 50 KB of chip RAM or less. So you are still able to save
  your work. If there isn't enough RAM for a requester the work will be saved
  to "Vokabi2:MemSave.voc")
@endnode

@node "desc_listWin" "Vokabi 2 guide - main window"
@next "desc_ask"
@prev "requires"
The main window of Vokabi 2 only consists of one listview gadget. It is moved
with the scroller gadget of the right window border. This listview gadget
contents either all words or all mistakes. You can see at the top border of
the window which mode is active at the moment.

The first two columns of the table are in both modes the first meanings of the
foreign and English language.

If you are in word mode and the third column contents a "<-" the word is a
reference. You can find and edit the original word by using @{"do reference" link "menu_find" 20}

If you are in mistake mode the number in the last column shows how many times
the word has to be answered correctly until the mistake entry is deleted.



There are the following pulldown menus:


    @{" Project " link "menu_project" 0}
    @{" Word    " link "menu_word" 0}
    @{" Search  " link "menu_find" 0}
    @{" Output  " link "menu_print" 0}
    @{" Mode    " link "menu_mode" 0}
@endnode

@node "menu_project" "Vokabi 2 guide - project menu "
@toc "desc_listWin"
@next "menu_word"
@prev "desc_listWin"
There are the following menu items available in the pulldown menu "Project":


  @{u}New@{uu}
    delete all words and mistakes and initialize the file settings
  @{u}Open - file@{uu}
    load a file
  @{u}Open - add file@{uu}
    load the words and unit marks of a file and addes them at the
    bottom of the actual file.
  @{u}Save@{uu}
    save all data
  @{u}Save as@{uu}
    save all data and gives a new name to the file
  @{u}File settings@{uu}
    open the @{"file settings window" link "win_fileset" 0}

  @{u}Global settings - change@{uu}
    open the @{"global settings window" link "win_globprefs" 0}
  @{u}Global settings - load@{uu}
    load the global settings from a file
  @{u}Global settings - save@{uu}
    save the global settings in a file
    The global settings are:
      - the contents of the pattern and directory gadget of the file
	requester
      - the settings in the @{"search requester" link "win_search" 0}
      - the settings in the @{"print requester" link "win_print" 0}.
    When the program is started the settings are read from the file
    "Vokabi2:Vokabi2.prefs".
  @{u}MUI Settings@{uu}
    open @{"MUI" link "mui" 0} settings requester.

  @{u}About@{uu}
    open about requester
  @{u}Über MUI@{uu}
    open @{"MUI" link "mui" 0} about requester

  @{u}Iconify@{uu}
    iconify Vokabi 2
  @{u}Quit@{uu}
    quit Vokabi 2
@endnode

@node "menu_word" "Vokabi 2 guide - word menu"
@toc "desc_listWin"
@next "menu_find"
@prev "menu_project"
There are the following menu items available in the pulldown menu "Word":


  @{u}look at / change@{uu}
    open @{"word requester" link "win_word" 0} which consists the
    actual word
    not available in mistake mode
  @{u}new@{uu}
    open @{"word requester" link "win_word" 0} for feeding new words
    not available in mistake mode
  @{u}delete@{uu}
    delete the active word or mistake

  @{u}unit marks@{uu}
    open @{"unit marks requester" link "win_unitmarks" 0}
    not available in mistake mode

  @{u}all words to unchecked@{uu}
    set the checked flag of every word to false
    not available in mistake mode
@endnode

@node "menu_find" "Vokabi 2 guide - search menu "
@toc "desc_listWin"
@next "menu_print"
@prev "menu_word"
There are the following menu items available in the pulldown menu "Search":

  @{u}word@{uu}
    open @{"search requester" link "win_search" 0}
    not available in mistake mode
  @{u}search next@{uu}
    search the next word which fits to the old values
    not available in mistake mode

  @{u}go to unit mark@{uu}
    open a window which contains all unit marks. After you have clicked
    on the button "Ok" the cursor is set to the selected unit mark.

  @{u}remember position@{uu}
    remember the actual active word.
  @{u}go to remembered position@{uu}
    make the remembered word the active word and remembers the old active
    word

  @{u}do reference@{uu}
    word mode:    make the original word of a reference the active word.
    mistake mode: make the original word of a mistake the active word.
@endnode

@node "menu_print" "Vokabi 2 guide - output menu"
@toc "desc_listWin"
@next "menu_mode"
@prev "menu_find"
There are the following menu items available in the pulldown menu "Output":


  @{u}print words@{uu}
    open @{"print requester" link "win_print" 0}
@endnode

@node "menu_mode" "Vokabi 2 guide - mode menu"
@toc "desc_listWin"
@next "desc_ask"
@prev "menu_print"
There are the following menu items available in the pulldown menu "Mode":


  @{u}edit words@{uu}
    go to word mode
  @{u}edit mistakes@{uu}
    go to mistake mode

  @{u}check words@{uu}
    go to @{"check mode" link "desc_ask" 0}
@endnode

@node "win_fileset" "Vokabi 2 guide - file settings requester"
@toc "menu_project"
@next "win_globprefs"
@prev "menu_project"
There are the following gadgets available in file settings requester:

@{u}check meanings@{uu}
  If this cycle gadget is set to "one" a listview gadget is shown when
  you are checked with the according direction. It contains ten words. One
  is the right one.
  If it is set to "all" there will be as many string gadgets as the word
  has got meanings. The meanings have to be filled in. When you are asked
  with the other direction only the first meaning will be shown. The other
  ones have to be filled in. This is suitable for training grammar.

@{u}order@{uu}
  If this cycle is set to "important" the order of the meanings you fill
  into the string gadgets in check mode will be checked. If it is set to
  "no matter" this won't happen.

@{u}name of language@{uu}
  You should feed the name of the language into this gadget. It is shown
  e.g in the headings of @{"word requester" link "win_word" 0}, @{"ask" link "desc_ask" 0} window
  or in the page heading of all @{"printouts" link "win_print" 0}.

@{u}seperating mark@{uu}
  If more than one meanings fit to one line in @{"printouts" link "win_print" 0} they
  are seperated by the string you have put in. If you want to see a space
  char after it you have to fill it, too!

@{u}relation of checking directions@{uu}
  You can set here in which direction you want to be checked. If you have
  set this gadget to 50% both directions are used equal. If it is set to
  100% English you'll only be asked foreign language -> English. If it is
  set to 0% English this is reverse.

@{u}Ok@{uu}
  remember settings and close the requester

@{u}Cancel@{uu}
  close the requester
@endnode

@node "win_globprefs" "Vokabi 2 guide - global settings requester"
@toc "menu_project"
@next "menu_word"
@prev "win_fileset"
There are only three gadgets available in global settings requester yet:

@{u}priority@{uu}
  You can set the priority of Vokabi 2 here.

@{u}Ok@{uu}
  remember settings and close the requester

@{u}Cancel@{uu}
  close the requester
@endnode

@node "win_word" "Vokabi 2 guide - word requester"
@toc "menu_word"
@next "win_unitmarks"
@prev "menu_word"
The word requester consists of two columns. Each one has got eight string
gadgets. You feed the single meanings into them - the foreign language is on
the left side, English on the other one.

@{u}part of speech@{uu}
  You set the part of speech of the word with this cycle gadget. It is
  important in check mode.

@{u}Genus@{uu}
  If the word is a noun you should set the gender of the word here.

@{u}set reference@{uu}
  Make the word a reference to the actual @{"word" link "desc_listWin" 0}.
  You can't set references on references. The word to which the reference
  is pointing is shown in the text gadget on the left side.
  If you make a mistake when you are asked a reference the fault isn't
  assigned to the reference but to the word the reference points to. It is
  easier to feed words which shall only be repeated this way.

@{u}delete reference@{uu}
  Make a reference to a normal word.


@{u}Ok@{uu}
  If the word requester is opened for editing an existing word the window
  is closed and the changes are remembered.
  If it is opened for feeding a new word a new word will be allocated after
  the actual @{"word" link "desc_listWin" 0}. It has got all data you have
  fed, but the window isn't closed, so you can feed the next word directly.

@{u}Cancel@{uu}
  close the requester without remembering anything
@endnode

@node "win_unitmarks" "Vokabi 2 guide - unit marks requester"
@toc "menu_word"
@next "menu_find"
@prev "win_word"
There are the following gadgets available in unit marks requester:

@{u}unit marks@{uu}
  This is a table of all unit marks. You choose which unit mark is to be
  edited here.

@{u}new@{uu}
  insert a new unit mark after the actual unit mark

@{u}delete@{uu}
  delete the actual unit mark

@{u}description@{uu}
  This string gadget can be activated by pressing space. You set the
  description of the unit mark here. The new description is only remembered
  if you leave the gadget by pressing return.

@{u}take position@{uu}
  Set unit mark to the active @{"word" link "desc_listWin" 0}. This word is also
  shown in the text gadget which is left of this button.

@{u}Ok@{uu}
  close the requester. The changes are remembered. They are also remembered
  if you leave the window by clicking on the close gadget of the window.
@endnode

@node "win_search" "Vokabi 2 guide - search requester"
@toc "menu_find"
@next "menu_print"
@prev "menu_find"
There are the following gadgets available in search requester:

@{u}search for@{uu}
  You have to feed the text you want to search for into this gadget. You
  may use patterns which may consist of the signs #?%~()|[]. You can't use
  the asterisk *, but it can be replaced by #?.

@{u}search in@{uu}
  foreign language: search in foreign meanings
  English:          search in English meanings
  both:             search in both languages

@{u}search direction@{uu}
  Top:              search forwards starting at the first word
  Bottom:           search backwards starting at the last word
  Cursor forwards:  search forwards starting at the active word
  Cursor backwards: search backwards starting at the active word

@{u}case sensitive@{uu}
  If this gadget is set you'll search case sensitively.

@{u}only first meaning@{uu}
  If this gadget is set you'll search only in the first meanings of all
  selected languages, otherwise you'll search in all meanings.

@{u}Ok@{uu}
  close the requester and start searching

@{u}Cancel@{uu}
  close the requester
@endnode

@node "win_print" "Vokabi 2 guide - print requester"
@toc "menu_print"
@next "menu_mode"
@prev "menu_print"
There are the following gadgets available in search requester:

@{u}density / condensed / quality / height of line@{uu}
  You can set the printing type the printer should use.
  The settings of these gadgets are passed to the printer directly.

@{u}chars per line / lines per page@{uu}
  You should set the space which is available on a page to this gadgets.
  You must consider the upper settings. You mustn't substract the borders!

@{u}border@{uu}
  Set the borders.
  @{u}top / bottom:@{uu} lines
  @{u}left / right:@{uu} columns

@{u}number of first page@{uu}
  The pages are numbered. You set the number of the first printed page here.
  This allows continuous numbering of your vocabulary pages.

@{u}heading@{uu}
  A heading can be printed at the top of the first page. You have to feed it
  to this gadget if you want to have one.

@{u}words to print@{uu}
  There are two popup listview gadgets containing the unit marks. You can
  specify the area whose words are to be printed. "Top" means the first
  word; "Bottom" means the last word

@{u}in File@{uu}
  If this gadget is set all words are written to a file. You specify its
  name by using the file requester popup gadget right of this checkbox.

@{u}Ok@{uu}
  start printing

@{u}Cancel@{uu}
  close requester
@endnode

@node "desc_ask" "Vokabi 2 guide - checking"
@next "desc_rexx"
@prev "desc_listWin"
The checking main window consists of two parts: There is the checking part
(the upper, larger one) and the state part (this is one line at the bottom).


The checking part may look different, according to the word which is checked
and to the file settings.


You can say:

  If there is a sting gadget you have to feed the according meaning. This
  check is case sensitive!

  If there is a listview gadget you have to choose the right meaning of the
  ten ones that are displayed.
  If there are ten words which are of the part of speech as the checked word
  the wrong meanings are of this part of speech. So you can't recognize the
  correct meaning by its part of speech.

  If the word is a noun you have to specify the right gender by using the
  cycle gadget down left.

  When you have filled all gadgets you should click the Ok gadget down right
  to check the word. If you have made a mistake you'll see the @{"correction" link "win_corr" 0}
  window.


The state part shows on its left side how many words you have answered right
and false. The counter is set to 0 by loading or making a new file. You can
alternatively click to "reset".

On the right side you choose the area whose words are to be checked. A unit
marks listview popup is used. The word on which the unit mark specified in the
ask end gadget is won't be cheked. "Top" means the first word; "Bottom" means
the last word of a file.
@endnode

@node "win_corr" "Vokabi 2 guide - making mistakes"
@toc "desc_ask"
@next "desc_rexx"
@prev "desc_ask"
If you have made a mistake the correction window appears. It only consists of
text gadgets which show you the meanings and gender of the word. When you
press Escape (Esc) or click on the close gadget the correction window will
disappear and checking will go on.


If you have made a mistake the word is inserted to the mistakes list. If there
has been no entry of this word before you have to give the right answer to the
word five times, then it's removed from the mistakes list. If you make another
mistake the counter will be raised by 3.

Words which have a high mistake counter are checked more often than words
which have a low one.
@endnode

@node "desc_rexx" "Vokabi 2 guide - Vokabi's ARexx port"
@next "todo"
@prev "desc_ask"
Vokabi 2's ARexx port is named VOKABI.1 . If Vokabi 2 is called a second time
this task will get VOKABI.2 as port name and so on.


There aren't many commands yet. If you want to get more commands I'll add as
many as you want. Up to now you can use:

  @{" HIDE   " link "rexx_hide" 0}
  @{" LOAD   " link "rexx_load" 0}
  @{" NEW    " link "rexx_new" 0}
  @{" QUIT   " link "rexx_quit" 0}
  @{" SAVE   " link "rexx_save" 0}
  @{" SAVEAS " link "rexx_saveas" 0}
  @{" SHOW   " link "rexx_show" 0}


You should also have a look at the documentation of MUI.
@endnode

@node "rexx_hide" "Vokabi 2 guide - ARexx command HIDE"
@toc "desc_rexx"
@next "rexx_load"
@prev "desc_rexx"

  @{b}HIDE@{ub}

arguments:  none

Iconify Vokabi 2. It is woken up by using @{"SHOW" link "rexx_show" 0}.
@endnode

@node "rexx_load" "Vokabi 2 guide - ARexx command LOAD"
@toc "desc_rexx"
@next "rexx_new"
@prev "rexx_hide"

  @{b}LOAD@{ub}

arguments:  FILENAME,FORCE/S

Load a file.

 FILENAME: Name of the file to be opened. If you omit this argument a file
	   requester will appear which asks you to specify a file.
 FORCE:    don't set security requesters
@endnode

@node "rexx_new" "Vokabi 2 guide - ARexx command NEW"
@toc "desc_rexx"
@next "rexx_quit"
@prev "rexx_load"

  @{b}NEW@{ub}

arguments:  FORCE/S

Delete all data and initialize file settings.

 FORCE: don't set security requesters
@endnode

@node "rexx_quit" "Vokabi 2 guide - ARexx command QUIT"
@toc "desc_rexx"
@next "rexx_save"
@prev "rexx_new"

  @{b}QUIT@{ub}

arguments:  FORCE/S

Quit Vokabi 2.

 FORCE: don't set security requesters
@endnode

@node "rexx_save" "Vokabi 2 guide - ARexx command SAVE"
@toc "desc_rexx"
@next "rexx_saveas"
@prev "rexx_quit"

  @{b}SAVE@{ub}

arguments:  none

Save the actual file. You can specify a new name by using @{"SAVEAS" link "rexx_saveas" 0}.
@endnode

@node "rexx_saveas" "Vokabi 2 guide - ARexx command SAVEAS"
@toc "desc_rexx"
@next "rexx_show"
@prev "rexx_save"

  @{b}SAVEAS@{ub}

arguments:  FILENAME

Save the actual file and set a new file name.

 FILENAME: The new name of the file. If you omit this argument a file
	   requester will appear and ask you to specify a new file name.

Using @{"SAVE" link "rexx_save" 0} uses the old file name.
@endnode

@node "rexx_show" "Vokabi 2 guide - ARexx command SHOW"
@toc "desc_rexx"
@next "todo"
@prev "rexx_saveas"

  @{b}SHOW@{ub}

arguments:  none

Wake Vokabi 2 up, when it is iconified.
@endnode

@node "todo" "Vokabi 2 guide - What is to do?"
@next "mui"
@prev "desc_rexx"
The next things I'll implement are:


- more ARexx commands

- possibility of changing the mistake counter of a word

- search for mistakes

- correction window: set the meanings where the mistake was off

- possibility of seting a string which is shown in checking mode for each
  word

- at least two unit marks for each file: "class test" and "short test". They
  won't be shown in printing.


If you have got another good idea please send it to @{"me" link "author" 0}.
@endnode

